<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,454,643,669]" box="[189,454,643,669]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,643,669]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,643,669]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,1399,691,861]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,564,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Cheilosia">
<emphasis box="[189,307,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[331,449,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Cheilosia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[472,564,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[578,678,691,717]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the following characters with other members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[189,301,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[189,301,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[310,376,727,753]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: antennal pits broadly separated, eye densely pilose, body pilosity not long and dense, body not bumble-bee like, and structural similarity of male genitalia. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1009,1217,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1009,1217,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Cheilosia hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1225,1316,764,790]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from other congeners by the unusual structure of the facial tubercle in combination with the colouration of femora.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,324,902,928]" box="[189,324,902,928]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,902,928]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,902,928]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,1398,949,1012]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
The new species is named after and in honour of Dr Martin Hauser, who collected an impressive amount of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[221,340,986,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[377,447,986,1012]" name="Nepal" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and allowed us to study the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[782,894,986,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,894,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
